data.title: Long term care workers at Bisset Court in Cole Harbour, NS vote 100% in favor of strike with CUPE 4970 due to understaffing.
data.description: In Cole Harbour, NS, long term care workers at Bisset Court, represented by CUPE 4970, have unanimously voted in favor of a strike mandate. All votes cast were in support of potential job action. The workers are advocating for fair wages and better recruitment and retention strategies to address understaffing problems in the sector. Trina Walker, President of CUPE 4970, highlighted the frequent short staffing issues, noting that it's a rare occurrence to have a fully staffed roster. The unanimous vote reflects the strong stance taken by workers in demanding improvements in their working conditions.
